name: JobNab
overview:
JobNab provides job seekers with a personally matched list of jobs available in their area.

JobNab utilizes a team of over 1,000 Job Scouts in over 250 U.S. markets to identify and submit only the best jobs. This spares job seekers the frustration of dealing with business opportunities, positions requiring a fee, or just outright scams.

JobNab Scouts are the backbone of our system. Every day they root out the best opportunities from every source imaginable to match with our pool of talented job seekers. Their careful attention to detail ensures that only quality jobs are entered into the system.

Our nationwide network of scouts tirelessly scour local sources in search of open positions that meet JobNab’s strict criteria for jobs that can be offered to our applicants. First and foremost each listing must be for a legitimate, paying job; no business opportunities, jobs that require upfront fees, or any other scams are allowed.

These jobs are then carefully matched to our job seekers based on a number of criteria. This guarantees that each applicant is presented with a personalized list of ideal opportunities that best fits his or her interests and skills.
